## dictReduce() function

Iterate over a dictionary to incrementally create a single value

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
export declare function dictReduce<T, R>(from: Dict<T>, reducer: IReducerFn<T, R>, initialVal: R): R;
```

## Parameters

|  Parameter | Type | Description |
|  --- | --- | --- |
|  from | <code>Dict&lt;T&gt;</code> | dictionary to iterate over |
|  reducer | <code>IReducerFn&lt;T, R&gt;</code> | reducer function |
|  initialVal | <code>R</code> | initial value that the accumulator starts with |
